# Category-Aware QA Evaluation Router

Code and data for the MSc thesis *Category-Aware Evaluation Architecture for
QA Systems: Routing Between Symbolic and Semantic Computation* (University of
Tartu, 2026).

The repository bundles the full experiment pipeline: synthetic benchmark
generation, router training and calibration across ten classifier
configurations, end-to-end evaluation against LLM and tool-augmented
baselines, and every result file cited in the thesis.

## Requirements

- Python 3.13
- An OpenAI API key (Phases 1, 3, 4)
- An Anthropic API key (Phase 4 secondary-generator and tool-augmented sweep)

## Setup

```bash
git clone <repo>
cd <repo>
conda create -n research python=3.13 && conda activate research
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .
cp .env.example .env
# edit .env: set OPENAI_API_KEY and ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
```

`pip install -e .` registers `thesis_router`, `benchmark`, `router`, and
`evaluation` as importable packages and makes `config` available at the top
level, so scripts can be run with `python -m scripts.<subdir>.<name>` from
any working directory.

## Reproduce

```bash
make phase1     # regenerate synthetic dataset with GPT-5.2 (non-deterministic)
make phase2     # train 10 router classifiers; outputs models/ + results/router/
make phase3     # end-to-end evaluation on 305 pairs; outputs results/e2e/
make phase4     # reasoning + tool-augmented baselines
make figures    # rebuild every thesis figure into figures/
```

`make all` runs phases 1–4 plus figures.

Individual scripts can be invoked directly:

```bash
python -m scripts.baselines.reasoning_model_comparison
python -m scripts.baselines.tool_augmented_llm_sweep --models gpt-4o-mini gpt-4o
python -m scripts.validation.secondary_generator --model sonnet
python -m scripts.analyses.tau_sensitivity
```

## Committed artefacts

`data/`, `models/`, and `results/` ship with the exact synthetic dataset,
trained classifiers, and result files that produced the numbers reported in
the thesis. Phases 2–4 reproduce deterministically from these (seed 42 in
`config.py`).

Phase 1 calls GPT-5.2 and is non-deterministic by design. Re-running it
produces a different synthetic dataset with the same distributional
properties; Phase 2 will then train on the fresh dataset.

## Cost estimate

API spend for a full re-run, based on token counts in the committed result
files and public provider pricing (2026):

| Phase | Work | Rough cost |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | regenerate ~4k synthetic prompts via GPT-5.2 | $20–50 |
| 3 | end-to-end evaluation, GPT-4o-mini + GPT-4o on 305 pairs | $1–3 |
| 4a | reasoning-model comparison (250 calls × 3 models) | $10–15 |
| 4b | tool-augmented sweep (175 pairs × 6 models) | $70–100 |

Budget **$100–200** for a complete re-run, with most of the spend on
Claude Opus in Phase 4b. Phases 2 and 5 cost nothing beyond compute: Phase 2
trains classifiers locally on the committed dataset, Phase 5 processes the
committed annotation CSVs.

If `gpt-5.2` is not available to you, substitute `gpt-4o` for Phase 1 by
editing `GENERATION_MODEL` in `config.py`.

## Layout

```
config.py              # paths, thresholds, constants
thesis_router/         # LLM client factories (OpenAI + Anthropic from env)
benchmark/             # synthetic benchmark construction
router/                # router training, calibration, evaluation
evaluation/            # deterministic functions + end-to-end harness
notebooks/             # Marimo phase notebooks
cli/                   # plain-Python entry points for each phase
scripts/
  baselines/           # LLM and tool-augmented baselines
  validation/          # synthetic-data validation, oracle audits, secondary generators
  analyses/            # tau, sensitivity, kappa, hyperparameters, parameter extraction
  artifacts/           # holdout, annotation CSVs, figures
data/                  # datasets (committed)
models/                # trained router artefacts (committed)
results/               # experiment outputs cited in the thesis (committed)
figures/               # publication PDFs (committed)
```

## Key thresholds

All thresholds live in `config.py`.

| Parameter | Value | Note |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Stratified split | 70 / 15 / 15 | Validation fold sized for stable Platt scaling |
| Keyword leakage | 0.25 | Reject if any token predicts >25% of one category |
| Dataset rejection | 0.80 F1 | Reject if regex baseline exceeds this Macro-F1 |
| Semantic dedup | 0.99 cosine | Removes near-identical LLM paraphrases |
| Noise mix | 60 / 25 / 10 / 5% | none / light / medium / heavy |
| Confidence tau | 0.85 | Validation-set sweep on routed accuracy and coverage |
| Bootstrap | 5,000 iters | 95% CIs |

